aff at this time in the room, while supervision is REQUIRED BY LAW for all other events within the school which students attend. &#10;An exemption is being made here that is not extended to other groups. It isn't so much a right or wrong issue, but the fact is you either have to (1) make the prayer time available to anyone (Muslim or not)... or (2) allow all religious groups to have specialized rooms for prayers led by non-school employees, unsupervised by staff, if they show interest. Failing that no religious group should be allowed in the school. &#10;You can't allow one group to do this and not others."/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="904" language="en" documentId="1407" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="SWOntMan" docType="artcomment" origUrl="http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/tempers-flare-over-prayer-in-schools-1.1104775" topic="prayer-in-schools" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="1407" notes="" title="Tempers flare over prayer in schools"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="269"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="270" end="428"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="429" end="851"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="51" sofa="1" begin="852" end="904"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47 51"/></xmi:XMI>